{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"The Hindus say, \"Nada brahma,\""},{"time":3000,"text":"one translation of which is, \"The world is sound.\""},{"time":6000,"text":"And in a way, that's true, because everything is vibrating."},{"time":9000,"text":"In fact, all of you as you sit here right now are vibrating."},{"time":12000,"text":"Every part of your body is vibrating at different frequencies."},{"time":15000,"text":"So you are, in fact, a chord --"},{"time":17000,"text":"each of you an individual chord."},{"time":19000,"text":"One definition of health may be"},{"time":21000,"text":"that that chord is in complete harmony."},{"time":23000,"text":"Your ears can't hear that chord;"},{"time":25000,"text":"they can actually hear amazing things. Your ears can hear 10 octaves."},{"time":28000,"text":"Incidentally, we see just one octave."},{"time":31000,"text":"Your ears are always on -- you have no ear lids."},{"time":33000,"text":"They work even when you sleep."},{"time":35000,"text":"The smallest sound you can perceive"},{"time":37000,"text":"moves your eardrum just four atomic diameters."},{"time":40000,"text":"The loudest sound you can hear"},{"time":42000,"text":"is a trillion times more powerful than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"Ears are made not for hearing,"},{"time":46000,"text":"but for listening."},{"time":48000,"text":"Listening is an active skill,"},{"time":50000,"text":"whereas hearing is passive, listening is something that we have to work at --"},{"time":53000,"text":"it's a relationship with sound."},{"time":55000,"text":"And yet it's a skill that none of us are taught."},{"time":57000,"text":"For example, have you ever considered that there are listening positions,"},{"time":60000,"text":"places you can listen from?"},{"time":62000,"text":"Here are two of them."},{"time":64000,"text":"Reductive listening is listening \"for.\""},{"time":66000,"text":"It reduces everything down to what's relevant"},{"time":69000,"text":"and it discards everything that's not relevant."},{"time":71000,"text":"Men typically listen reductively."},{"time":73000,"text":"So he's saying, \"I've got this problem.\""},{"time":75000,"text":"He's saying, \"Here's your solution. Thanks very much. Next.\""},{"time":77000,"text":"That's the way we talk, right guys?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"Expansive listening, on the other hand,"},{"time":81000,"text":"is listening \"with,\" not listening \"for.\""},{"time":83000,"text":"It's got no destination in mind --"},{"time":85000,"text":"it's just enjoying the journey."},{"time":87000,"text":"Women typically listen expansively."},{"time":89000,"text":"If you look at these two, eye contact, facing each other,"},{"time":91000,"text":"possibly both talking at the same time."},{"time":93000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":96000,"text":"Men, if you get nothing else out of this talk,"},{"time":98000,"text":"practice expansive listening,"},{"time":100000,"text":"and you can transform your relationships."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"The trouble with listening is that so much of what we hear"},{"time":105000,"text":"is noise, surrounding us all the time."},{"time":108000,"text":"Noise like this, according to the European Union,"},{"time":111000,"text":"is reducing the health and the quality of life"},{"time":113000,"text":"of 25 percent"},{"time":115000,"text":"of the population of Europe."},{"time":117000,"text":"Two percent of the population of Europe --"},{"time":119000,"text":"that's 16 million people --"},{"time":121000,"text":"are having their sleep devastated"},{"time":123000,"text":"by noise like that."},{"time":125000,"text":"Noise kills"},{"time":127000,"text":"200,000 people a year in Europe."},{"time":129000,"text":"It's a really big problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"Now, when you were little, if you had noise and you didn't want to hear it,"},{"time":133000,"text":"you'd stick your fingers in your ears and hum."},{"time":135000,"text":"These days, you can do a similar thing, it just looks a bit cooler."},{"time":138000,"text":"It looks a bit like this."},{"time":140000,"text":"The trouble with widespread headphone use"},{"time":142000,"text":"is it brings three really big health issues."},{"time":145000,"text":"The first really big health issue is a word that Murray Schafer coined:"},{"time":148000,"text":"\"schizophonia.\""},{"time":150000,"text":"It's a dislocation"},{"time":152000,"text":"between what you see and what you hear."},{"time":154000,"text":"So, we're inviting into our lives"},{"time":156000,"text":"the voices of people who are not present with us."},{"time":159000,"text":"I think there's something deeply unhealthy"},{"time":161000,"text":"about living all the time in schizophonia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"The second problem that comes with headphone abuse"},{"time":165000,"text":"is compression."},{"time":167000,"text":"We squash music to fit it into our pocket"},{"time":169000,"text":"and there is a cost attached to this."},{"time":171000,"text":"Listen to this -- this is an uncompressed piece of music."},{"time":174000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":180000,"text":"And now the same piece of music with 98 percent of the data removed."},{"time":183000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":187000,"text":"I do hope that some of you at least"},{"time":189000,"text":"can hear the difference between those two."},{"time":191000,"text":"There is a cost of compression."},{"time":193000,"text":"It makes you tired and irritable to have to make up all of that data."},{"time":195000,"text":"You're having to imagine it."},{"time":197000,"text":"It's not good for you in the long run."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"The third problem with headphones is this: deafness --"},{"time":202000,"text":"noise-induced hearing disorder."},{"time":204000,"text":"Ten million Americans already have this for one reason or another,"},{"time":207000,"text":"but really worryingly,"},{"time":209000,"text":"16 percent --"},{"time":211000,"text":"roughly one in six -- of American teenagers"},{"time":213000,"text":"suffer from noise-induced hearing disorder"},{"time":215000,"text":"as a result of headphone abuse."},{"time":218000,"text":"One study at an American university"},{"time":220000,"text":"found that 61 percent of college freshmen"},{"time":223000,"text":"had damaged hearing"},{"time":225000,"text":"as a result of headphone abuse."},{"time":227000,"text":"We may be raising an entire generation of deaf people."},{"time":230000,"text":"Now that's a really serious problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"I'll give you three quick tips to protect your ears"},{"time":234000,"text":"and pass these on to your children, please."},{"time":236000,"text":"Professional hearing protectors are great;"},{"time":238000,"text":"I use some all the time."},{"time":240000,"text":"If you're going to use headphones, buy the best ones you can afford"},{"time":243000,"text":"because quality means you don't have to have it so loud."},{"time":245000,"text":"If you can't hear somebody talking to you in a loud voice,"},{"time":247000,"text":"it's too loud."},{"time":249000,"text":"And thirdly, if you're in bad sound,"},{"time":251000,"text":"it's fine to put your fingers in your ears or just move away from it."},{"time":253000,"text":"Protect your ears in that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"Let's move away from bad sound and look at some friends that I urge you to seek out."},{"time":258000,"text":"WWB:"},{"time":260000,"text":"Wind, water, birds --"},{"time":263000,"text":"stochastic natural sounds"},{"time":265000,"text":"composed of lots of individual random events,"},{"time":268000,"text":"all of it very healthy,"},{"time":270000,"text":"all of it sound that we evolved to over the years."},{"time":272000,"text":"Seek those sounds out; they're good for you and so it this."},{"time":278000,"text":"Silence is beautiful."},{"time":280000,"text":"The Elizabethans described language"},{"time":282000,"text":"as decorated silence."},{"time":284000,"text":"I urge you to move away from silence with intention"},{"time":287000,"text":"and to design soundscapes just like works of art."},{"time":290000,"text":"Have a foreground, a background, all in beautiful proportion."},{"time":293000,"text":"It's fun to get into designing with sound."},{"time":295000,"text":"If you can't do it yourself, get a professional to do it for you."},{"time":298000,"text":"Sound design is the future,"},{"time":300000,"text":"and I think it's the way we're going to change the way the world sounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"I'm going to just run quickly through eight modalities,"},{"time":305000,"text":"eight ways sound can improve health."},{"time":308000,"text":"First, ultrasound: we're very familiar with it from physical therapy;"},{"time":311000,"text":"it's also now being used to treat cancer."},{"time":313000,"text":"Lithotripsy -- saving thousands of people a year from the scalpel"},{"time":316000,"text":"by pulverizing stones with high-intensity sound."},{"time":319000,"text":"Sound healing is a wonderful modality."},{"time":321000,"text":"It's been around for thousands of years."},{"time":323000,"text":"I do urge you to explore this."},{"time":325000,"text":"There are great things being done there, treating now autism,"},{"time":327000,"text":"dementia and other conditions."},{"time":329000,"text":"And music, of course. Just listening to music is good for you,"},{"time":332000,"text":"if it's music that's made with good intention,"},{"time":334000,"text":"made with love, generally."},{"time":336000,"text":"Devotional music, good -- Mozart, good."},{"time":338000,"text":"There are all sorts of types of music"},{"time":340000,"text":"that are very healthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"And four modalities where you need to take some action"},{"time":344000,"text":"and get involved."},{"time":346000,"text":"First of all, listen consciously."},{"time":348000,"text":"I hope that that after this talk you'll be doing that."},{"time":350000,"text":"It's a whole new dimension to your life and it's wonderful to have that dimension."},{"time":353000,"text":"Secondly, get in touch with making some sound --"},{"time":356000,"text":"create sound."},{"time":358000,"text":"The voice is the instrument we all play,"},{"time":360000,"text":"and yet how many of us are trained in using our voice? Get trained;"},{"time":363000,"text":"learn to sing, learn to play an instrument."},{"time":365000,"text":"Musicians have bigger brains -- it's true."},{"time":368000,"text":"You can do this in groups as well."},{"time":370000,"text":"It's a fantastic antidote to schizophonia;"},{"time":372000,"text":"to make music and sound in a group of people,"},{"time":374000,"text":"whichever style you enjoy particularly."},{"time":377000,"text":"And let's take a stewarding role for the sound around us."},{"time":379000,"text":"Protect your ears? Yes, absolutely."},{"time":381000,"text":"Design soundscapes to be beautiful around you"},{"time":383000,"text":"at home and at work."},{"time":385000,"text":"And let's start to speak up"},{"time":387000,"text":"when people are assailing us"},{"time":389000,"text":"with the noise that I played you early on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"So I'm going to leave you with seven things you can do right now"},{"time":394000,"text":"to improve your health with sound."},{"time":396000,"text":"My vision is of a world that sounds beautiful"},{"time":399000,"text":"and if we all start doing these things,"},{"time":401000,"text":"we will take a very big step in that direction."},{"time":403000,"text":"So I urge you to take that path."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"I'm leaving you with a little more birdsong, which is very good for you."},{"time":408000,"text":"I wish you sound health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}